quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  78,31,"Verily, for the pious is a blissful place"
  78,32,gardens and vineyards
  78,33,and girls with swelling breasts of the same age as themselves
  78,34,and a brimming cup
  78,35,they shall hear therein no folly and no lie
  78,36,"a reward from thy Lord, a sufficient gift"
  78,37,"The Lord of the heavens and the earth, and what is between them both,- the Merciful,- they cannot obtain audience of Him"
  78,38,"The day when the Spirit and the angels shall stand in ranks, they shall not speak save to whom the Merciful permits, and who speaks aright"
  78,39,That is the true day; and whoso pleases let him take to a resort unto his Lord
  78,40,"Verily, we have warned you of a torment that is nigh: on a day when man shall see what his two hands have sent forward; and the misbeliever shall say, 'Would that I were dust"